A model and fashion blogger who was horrifically injured after walking into a spinning plane propeller has taken her first steps after the accident.

A post on Lauren Scruggs' Caring Bridge website reveals she had managed 30 steps five days after she inadvertently walked into the propeller at a private airport in Dallas, Texas.

The 23-year-old suffered a skull fracture, brain injury, severed left hand and could still lose her left eye in the horrific incident.

