The update added: 'The left eye is still non-responsive, the doctors will continue monitoring it for the next few days.

'Please pray [for] Lauren as she begins to learn the extent of her injuries.'

She is believed to have been returning to the two-seater plane to thank the pilot when she accidentally walked into the propeller.

Her father Jeff told Good Morning America: 'They're telling us it's going to be a long recovery. Obviously she's had a lot of trauma to her head, and she lost her left hand and her left eye is questionable.

'We're praying she'll regain her sight.'

